{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PadControllerProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/EventControllerProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3Gtk23EventControllerProtocolP","text":"EventControllerProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pads are the collection of buttons and tactile sensors often found around"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the stylus-sensitive area."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"These buttons and sensors have no implicit meaning, and by default they"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"perform no action. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkPadController"},{"type":"text","text":" is provided to map those to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Action"},{"type":"text","text":"] objects, thus letting the application give them a more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"semantic meaning."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons and sensors are not constrained to triggering a single action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDK_SOURCE_TABLET_PAD"},{"type":"text","text":" devices feature multiple “modes”. All these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"input elements have one current mode, which may determine the final action"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"being triggered."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pad devices often divide buttons and sensors into groups. All elements"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in a group share the same current mode, but different groups may have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different modes. See [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.DevicePad.get_n_groups"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gdk.DevicePad.get_group_n_modes"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each of the actions that a given button\/strip\/ring performs for a given mode"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is defined by a [struct"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.PadActionEntry"},{"type":"text","text":"]. It contains an action name that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be looked up in the given [iface"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":"] and activated whenever"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the specified input element and mode are triggered."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A simple example of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkPadController"},{"type":"text","text":" usage: Assigning button 1 in all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modes and pad devices to an “invert-selection” action:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["GtkPadActionEntry *pad_actions[] = {","  { GTK_PAD_ACTION_BUTTON, 1, -1, \"Invert selection\", \"pad-actions.invert-selection\" },","  …","};","","…","action_group = g_simple_action_group_new ();","action = g_simple_action_new (\"pad-actions.invert-selection\", NULL);","g_signal_connect (action, \"activate\", on_invert_selection_activated, NULL);","g_action_map_add_action (G_ACTION_MAP (action_group), action);","…","pad_controller = gtk_pad_controller_new (action_group, NULL);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The actions belonging to rings\/strips will be activated with a parameter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_DOUBLE"},{"type":"text","text":" bearing the value of the given axis, it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is required that those are made stateful and accepting this "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVariantType"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PadControllerProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkPadController"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PadController"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PadControllerRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/padcontrollerprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/EventControllerProtocol","doc:\/\/Gtk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/PadController","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/PadControllerRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/PadControllerProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"